I"D<p><strong>Michael Jeffrey Jordan</strong> (born February 17, 1963), also known by his initials <strong>MJ</strong>,<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan#cite_note-11">[8]</a> is an American businessman and former professional <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basketball" title="Basketball">basketball</a> player, who is currently a minority owner of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charlotte_Hornets" title="Charlotte Hornets">Charlotte Hornets</a> of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Basketball_Association" title="National Basketball Association">National Basketball Association</a> (NBA). He played 15 seasons in the NBA between 1984 and 2003, winning six <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NBA_championships" title="NBA championships">NBA championships</a> with the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chicago_Bulls" title="Chicago Bulls">Chicago Bulls</a>. Widely considered to be one of the greatest players of all time,<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan#cite_note-12">[9]</a><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan#cite_note-13">[10]</a><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan#cite_note-14">[11]</a> he was integral in popularizing basketball and the NBA around the world in the 1980s and 1990s,<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan#cite_note-Markovits-15">[12]</a> becoming a global <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cultural_icon" title="Cultural icon">cultural icon</a>.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan#cite_note-16">[13]</a></p>
